reviews.text: 1-3 meters away from station entrance gates  - in the passage, where smoking is prohibited and where is live departure screen  - people are constantly smoking cigarretes and forcing other pedestrians or overground users to breath all that toxic fumes in partially enclosed zone. TFL staff sees that and they ignoring it. It is agains the law to smoke in that area. Also there is no lift to get up to the platform and the staris are quite steep. Not to mention that trains to Gospel oak or Barking run every 15 - 30 minutes.
